  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="badge badge-orange">VPS Install Guide</span>
      <h1>Install on a VPS</h1>
      <p class="page-subtitle">Run OpenClaw on a cloud server for 24/7 availability, zero battery drain, and rock-solid stability. The best setup for serious users.</p>
      <div class="lang-notice">
        <a href="/zh/guide/install-vps">üáπüáº Èñ±ËÆÄ‰∏≠ÊñáÁâà</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">
        <aside class="toc">
          <div class="toc-inner">
            <div class="toc-title">On This Page</div>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="#why-vps">Why VPS?</a></li>
              <li><a href="#providers">Choose a Provider</a></li>
              <li><a href="#ssh">Connect via SSH</a></li>
              <li><a href="#nodejs">Install Node.js</a></li>
              <li><a href="#openclaw">Install OpenClaw</a></li>
              <li><a href="#daemon">Set Up Daemon</a></li>
              <li><a href="#faq">FAQ</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </aside>

        <article class="article">

          <!-- Why VPS -->
          <section id="why-vps" class="article-section">
            <h2>Why Run OpenClaw on a VPS?</h2>
            <div class="why-grid">
              <div class="why-card">
                <div class="why-icon">‚è∞</div>
                <h3>24/7 Uptime</h3>
                <p>Your AI is always available ‚Äî even when your laptop is closed, on a plane, or out of battery. Never miss a message.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="why-card">
                <div class="why-icon">üîã</div>
                <h3>Zero Battery Drain</h3>
                <p>A VPS sips power from the data center. Your personal devices stay charged and free for other tasks.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="why-card">
                <div class="why-icon">üõ°Ô∏è</div>
                <h3>Stable & Reliable</h3>
                <p>Data centers have redundant power and internet. No connection drops, no kernel updates rebooting your AI mid-conversation.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="why-card">
                <div class="why-icon">üí∞</div>
                <h3>Affordable</h3>
                <p>A capable VPS costs $4‚Äì8/month ‚Äî less than most streaming subscriptions. Way worth it for a personal AI that's always on.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- Providers -->
          <section id="providers" class="article-section">
            <h2>Recommended VPS Providers</h2>
            <p>We recommend these two providers for their reliability, pricing, and beginner-friendly interfaces:</p>

            <div class="provider-cards">
              <div class="provider-card featured">
                <div class="provider-badge">Best for Beginners</div>
                <div class="provider-logo">üåê</div>
                <h3>Hostinger</h3>
                <div class="provider-price">From $4.99/month</div>
                <p>Clean UI, one-click Ubuntu setup, great support. Perfect if you've never used a VPS before.</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Ubuntu 22.04 LTS pre-installed</li>
                  <li>1 vCPU, 1 GB RAM (sufficient for OpenClaw)</li>
                  <li>Weekly backups included</li>
                  <li>Responsive 24/7 chat support</li>
                </ul>
                <a href="https://www.hostinger.com/vps-hosting" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-primary provider-btn">
                  Get Hostinger VPS ‚Üí
                </a>
                {/* AFFILIATE LINK - replace before launch */}
              </div>

              <div class="provider-card">
                <div class="provider-logo">üåä</div>
                <h3>DigitalOcean</h3>
                <div class="provider-price">From $6/month</div>
                <p>Developer-favorite with a clean API, excellent documentation, and reliable global infrastructure.</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>1-click Ubuntu Droplets</li>
                  <li>1 vCPU, 1 GB RAM</li>
                  <li>Automated backups available</li>
                  <li>$200 free credit for new accounts</li>
                </ul>
                <a href="https://m.do.co/c/43c344eea808" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-outline provider-btn">
                  Get DigitalOcean ‚Üí
                </a>
                {/* AFFILIATE LINK - replace before launch */}
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="tip-box">
              <strong>üí° What specs do I need?</strong> OpenClaw is lightweight. A 1 vCPU / 1 GB RAM / 20 GB SSD VPS is plenty for a personal setup with a few channels and one or two personas. Scale up only if you run a team deployment.
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- SSH -->
          <section id="ssh" class="article-section">
            <h2>Step 1: Connect via SSHÔºàÈÅ†Á´ØÈÄ£Á∑öÂ∑•ÂÖ∑ÔºåËÆì‰Ω†Âú®Ëá™Â∑±ÁöÑÈõªËÖ¶‰∏äÊéßÂà∂ÈÅ†ÊñπÁöÑ‰º∫ÊúçÂô®Ôºâ</h2>
            <p>Open a terminal on your computer (Terminal on Mac, or the Ubuntu window on Windows), then type:</p>
            <p>After creating your VPS (Ubuntu 22.04 LTS recommended), connect using the server's IP address from your provider's dashboard.</p>
            <pre><code>ssh root@YOUR_SERVER_IP</code></pre>

            <div class="terminal-preview">
              <div class="terminal-bar">
                <span class="dot dot-red"></span>
                <span class="dot dot-yellow"></span>
                <span class="dot dot-green"></span>
                <span class="terminal-title">Terminal ‚Äî ssh</span>
              </div>
              <pre class="terminal-body"><code><span class="t-prompt">$</span> ssh root@203.0.113.42
The authenticity of host '203.0.113.42' can't be established.
ECDSA key fingerprint is SHA256:abc123...
Are you sure you want to continue connecting? <span class="t-input">yes</span>
root@203.0.113.42's password: <span class="t-input">‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢</span>

Welcome to Ubuntu 22.04.3 LTS (GNU/Linux 5.15.0-88-generic x86_64)
root@openclaw-vps:~#</code></pre>
            </div>

            <p>Once connected, update the system:</p>
            <pre><code>apt update && apt upgrade -y</code></pre>

            <div class="tip-box">
              <strong>üîê Security tip:</strong> Consider setting up SSH key authentication and disabling password login after your first login. Ask your VPS provider's docs for instructions, or search "SSH key authentication Ubuntu".
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- Node.js -->
          <section id="nodejs" class="article-section">
            <h2>Step 2: Install Node.js</h2>
            <p>Install Node.js 22 using the NodeSource repository:</p>
            <pre><code>curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_22.x | sudo -E bash -
sudo apt-get install -y nodejs</code></pre>
            <p>Verify:</p>
            <pre><code>node --version   # v22.x.x
npm --version    # 10.x.x</code></pre>
          </section>

          <!-- OpenClaw -->
          <section id="openclaw" class="article-section">
            <h2>Step 3: Install OpenClaw</h2>
            <pre><code>npm install -g openclaw@latest
openclaw --version</code></pre>

            <p>Run the onboarding wizard:</p>
            <pre><code>openclaw onboard --install-daemon</code></pre>

            <p>The wizard will ask for your AI provider and API key, then configure your workspace at <code>~/.openclaw/workspace/</code>.</p>
          </section>

          <!-- Daemon -->
          <section id="daemon" class="article-section">
            <h2>Step 4: Set Up the Daemon</h2>
            <p>On a VPS, the daemon is critical. It ensures OpenClaw starts automatically after server reboots and restarts if it crashes.</p>

            <StepCard number={1} title="Verify the daemon is running">
              <pre><code>openclaw gateway status</code></pre>
              <p>You should see:</p>
              <pre><code>‚óè openclaw-gateway.service - OpenClaw Gateway
   Loaded: loaded (/etc/systemd/system/openclaw-gateway.service)
   Active: active (running) since Mon 2026-02-22 10:00:00 UTC</code></pre>
            </StepCard>

            <StepCard number={2} title="Connect your channels">
              <pre><code>openclaw channels login</code></pre>
              <p>Follow the <a href="/guide/telegram">Telegram guide</a> or <a href="/guide/whatsapp">WhatsApp guide</a> to connect your messaging platform.</p>
            </StepCard>

            <StepCard number={3} title="Access the Control UI remotely">
              <p>The gateway runs on port 18789. To access it securely from your laptop, open your terminal on your computer (Terminal on Mac, or the Ubuntu window on Windows) and run:</p>
              <p>üìã Copy this line directly ‚Äî you only need to change the IP at the end:</p>
              <pre><code>ssh -L 18789:localhost:18789 root@<strong>YOUR_SERVER_IP</strong></code></pre>
              <p style="font-size:0.88rem; color:var(--text2);">Replace <strong>YOUR_SERVER_IP</strong> with the IP address shown in your Hostinger/DigitalOcean control panel (e.g.: 203.0.113.42)</p>
              <p>What this command does: it creates a secure tunnel between your computer and the cloud server, so you can open a browser and control your AI. Think of it like a phone line connecting your computer to the remote server.</p>
              <p>Then open <a href="http://127.0.0.1:18789" target="_blank">http://127.0.0.1:18789</a> on your local machine.</p>
              <div class="tailscale-box">
                <h4>üòÖ Too complicated? Here's an easier way:</h4>
                <p>Install <a href="https://tailscale.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Tailscale</a> on both your VPS and your laptop. Tailscale creates a permanent, encrypted private network between your devices ‚Äî no complex SSH tunneling needed. Once set up, you can access the Control UI directly without typing the long command above.</p>
                <p>It's free for personal use and takes about 5 minutes to set up.</p>
              </div>
            </StepCard>

            <div class="success-box">
              <strong>‚úÖ Production Ready!</strong> Your OpenClaw instance is now running 24/7 on a cloud server. Messages arrive any time, and your AI responds instantly ‚Äî even when you're asleep.
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- FAQ -->
          <section id="faq" class="article-section">
            <h2>FAQ</h2>
            <div class="faq-list">
              <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                  Which Ubuntu version should I choose?
                  <span class="faq-arrow">‚ñº</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-a">
                  <p>Ubuntu 22.04 LTS (Jammy Jellyfish) is the recommended choice. It's stable, well-supported until April 2027, and all instructions here are tested on it. Avoid non-LTS versions for a server.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                  How do I update OpenClaw on my VPS?
                  <span class="faq-arrow">‚ñº</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-a">
                  <p>Connect to your server and run:</p>
                  <pre><code>npm install -g openclaw@latest
openclaw gateway restart</code></pre>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                  Is my data stored on the VPS?
                  <span class="faq-arrow">‚ñº</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-a">
                  <p>Yes ‚Äî OpenClaw stores conversation history, persona files, and workspace data on your VPS. It never leaves your server. Take periodic backups using your provider's snapshot feature.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="support-note">
              Having trouble? Join the <a href="https://discord.com/invite/clawd" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">OpenClaw Discord community</a> or <a href="https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">report an issue</a>.
            </div>
          </section>

          <div class="nav-buttons">
            <a href="/guide/install" class="btn btn-outline">‚Üê Choose Platform</a>
            <a href="/guide/telegram" class="btn btn-primary">Next: Choose Your Messaging Platform ‚Üí</a>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

